class Solution {
    public boolean isIsomorphic(String s, String t) {

        int map1[]=new int[200];
        int map2[]=new int[200];

        if(s.length()!=t.length())
            return false;


        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++)
        {
            if(map1[s.charAt(i)]!=map2[t.charAt(i)])
                return false;

            map1[s.charAt(i)]=i+1;
            map2[t.charAt(i)]=i+1;
        }
        return true;
    }
}


Two strings are called isomorphic if the characters in the first string can be replaced to get the second string.

Rules
Every character in the first string must map to only one character in the second string.
A character cannot map to two different characters.
Two different characters cannot map to the same character.
The order of characters must remain the same.
Algorithm
Create two HashMaps.
Traverse both strings together.
For every pair of characters:
Check if the mapping already exists.
If it exists and is different, return false.
Otherwise, store the mapping.
If all mappings are valid, return true.
